quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  38,65,"Say [O Prophet], “I am only a warner, and none has the right to be worshiped except Allah, the One, the Subjugator"
  38,66,"Lord of the heavens and earth and all that is between them, the All-Mighty, Most Forgiving.”"
  38,67,"Say, “This [Qur’an] is of great importance"
  38,68,from which you are turning away.”
  38,69,"[And say], “I had no knowledge of the highest assembly [of angels] when they were disputing [about Adam]"
  38,70,I have only received revelation in order to give a clear warning.”
  38,71,"[Remember] when your Lord said to the angels, “I am going to create a human being from clay"
  38,72,"When I completed his creation and breathed into him of My [created] soul, fall down in prostration to him.”"
  38,73,Then the angels fell down in prostration all together
  38,74,"except Iblīs, who was arrogant and became one of the disbelievers"
  38,75,"[Allah] said, “O Iblīs, what prevented you from prostrating to whom I created with My two Hands? Did you just became proud or have you always been arrogant?”"
  38,76,"He said, “I am better than him: You created me from fire and created him from clay.”"
  38,77,"[Allah] said, “Then get out of here, for you are accursed"
  38,78,and My curse will be upon you until the Day of Judgment.”
  38,79,"He said, “My Lord, then give me respite until the Day of their resurrection.”"
  38,80,"Allah said, “You are given respite"
  38,81,until the Day of the appointed time.”
  38,82,"Iblīs said, “By Your Might, I will surely mislead them all"
  38,83,except Your chosen slaves among them.”
  38,84,"Allah said, “This truth is – and I only say the truth –"
  38,85,that I will certainly fill Hell with you and those of them who follow you all together.”
  38,86,"Say [O Prophet], “I do not ask you for any reward for it, nor do I pretend to be what I am not"
  38,87,It is only a reminder for all people
  38,88,And you will surely know its truth after a while.”